# 5. PriorityQueue (Heap)

Maintains elements in priority order.

```java
PriorityQueue<Integer> pq = new PriorityQueue<>();
```

Default

```
Min Heap
```

Methods

```java
pq.offer(5);

pq.offer(2);

pq.offer(8);

pq.poll();

pq.peek();
```

Output

```
2
```

### Max Heap

```java
PriorityQueue<Integer> maxHeap =
    new PriorityQueue<>(Collections.reverseOrder());
```

Time Complexity

| Operation | Complexity |
|------------|------------|
| offer() | O(log n) |
| poll() | O(log n) |
| peek() | O(1) |

